Key Match Events: Mitch Marsh scored an unbeaten 177 off 132 balls
Marnus Labuschagne effected two smart run outs in Bangladesh's innings
Adam Zampa took the key wicket of Liton Das (36)
Sean Abbott took 2-61 in his first World Cup match
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh's performance will please Australia most
Marsh's century helped Australia pull off their biggest ever World Cup chase
Miscellaneous Highlights: Marnus Labuschagne did not have a chance to press his claims with the bat
Seve Smith struck a timely 63 not out
Smith and Marsh shared an unbeaten 175-run third-wicket stand
Adam Zampa (2-32) also continued his terrific tournament
